ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would definitely recommend any course on Benjamin, Kafka, and Hoelderlin to anyone who takes reading seriously, but I would and have recommended any course taught by Prof. Nagele to my fellows. He is an exceptional teacher.

The course is about close readings of German texts. A broad question is the relation between "life" and "literature" and in what ways these notions coincide and produce one another. I would recommend the class, but suggest that the student do extensive reading on her own in order to get the most out the the assigned readings.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: This course deepened my knowledge of a certain period of German literature and in particular of a certain author important to my research.
